# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

## Summary
Updated the Vercel Web Analytics integration to use the correct framework-specific import path for Next.js App Router as per the latest official documentation.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:
- **src/app/layout.tsx**: Updated the Analytics import from `@vercel/analytics/react` to `@vercel/analytics/next` to follow the official Next.js App Router integration pattern

### Updated Files:
- **package-lock.json**: Updated dependency resolution tree after running `npm install`

## Implementation Details

The project already had `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 installed and the Analytics component was already integrated in the root layout. However, it was using the generic React import (`@vercel/analytics/react`) instead of the Next.js-specific import (`@vercel/analytics/next`).

According to the latest Vercel Analytics documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), Next.js App Router applications should import from `@vercel/analytics/next` for optimal performance and framework-specific features.

### What This Import Does:
- Provides Next.js-specific optimizations for analytics tracking
- Automatically tracks page views and navigation events in the App Router
- Integrates with Next.js server components and streaming rendering
- Ensures proper analytics initialization during hydration

## Verification Steps Completed

1. ✅ Fetched latest documentation from Vercel
2. ✅ Identified project as Next.js App Router (src/app/layout.tsx)
3. ✅ Updated import to framework-specific path
4. ✅ Ran `npm install` to update lock files
5. ✅ Build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
6. ✅ Linter passed with no new errors (`npm run lint`)

## Next Steps

The Analytics component is now properly configured and will begin tracking page views once deployed to Vercel. To enable analytics data collection:

1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to your project's Analytics section in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click "Enable" if analytics aren't already enabled
4. Analytics data will begin appearing after users visit the deployed site

## Technical Notes

- The Analytics component is placed at the end of the `<body>` tag in the root layout, which is the recommended location
- No additional configuration is needed; the component works automatically
- Analytics requests will be visible in the browser's Network tab as requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`
